org.apache.chemistry.opencmis.server.support

Class MutableCallContextWrapper

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.chemistry.opencmis.server.support.MutableCallContextWrapper
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    CallContext, MutableCallContext

    public class MutableCallContextWrapper
extends Object
implements MutableCallContext
    Provides a convenient implementation of the MutableCallContext interface that can be subclassed by developers wishing to change, add, or hide call context data. If the provided CallContext object implements the MutableCallContext interface, all get(String), put(String, Object), and remove(String) calls are forwarded to this call context object. If this CallContext object does not implement the MutableCallContext interface, the key-value pairs are stored here and hide the values of the provided CallContext object. That is, the first MutableCallContext object in the chain of MutableCallContextWrapper objects manages the data.
